Burdened by a police investigation back home, and in turmoil about her choice to terminate her pregnancy, Jamie is haunted by Isaac's inter-dimensional visits as he persuades her to join him. title: The Search for Count Dante
des: FATHER OF US MIXED MARTIAL ARTS, HAIRDRESSER, and much more. In the 1960s and 70s, his scowl was unmistakable and his kung fu pose conveyed a menace that went beyond martial arts mastery. He called himself Count Dante and he claimed to be "The Deadliest Man Alive" in garish comic book ads and gruesome instructional manuals. While his name and title may have been more show biz than lineage, his drive to live up to his fearsome reputation left one man dead and a promising career in ruins. Count Dante's real name was John Keehan and he grew up in a posh section of Chicago. In the early 1960s he was one of the most intriguing figures in America's nascent martial arts scene. Bruce Lee and Chuck Norris were his contemporaries, but Keehan's appetite for self-promotion was greater than a movie star's. When he wasn't putting on karate tournaments, he was styling hair and courting Playboy Bunnies. He was one part "Black Belt Jones" and one part Warren Beatty from "Shampoo." He challenged Muhammad Ali, tested his hand speed against a quick draw artist, and kept an African lion as a house pet. But as the 1960s gave way to the 70s, Keehan could no longer separate himself from the macho marketing tool that he created. Rival dojos were stormed, the life of Keehan's best friend was lost and Dante became involved in the Purolator Armored Car Robbery in 1974 that netted four million dollars. Soon after the robbery, Dante mysteriously died and was buried in an unmarked grave.
cast: Jimmy Jones, Gene LeBell, Robert Wall

In Hell, or Tidewater this long-time dream has come true but there's a twist; once the oil makes it the shores of BC it is not being transported by traditional Tanker but by giant submarines called S.U.L.C.C.s or Submersible Ultra Large Crude Carriers. Things start to get interesting when a camera crew shows up to film an episode of Humongous Boats (a fictional version of the popular show Mighty Ships) and encounter more than just the run of the mill giant ship overview they were hoping to film. Turns out the Russians view the Canadian enterprise as a threat to their energy hegemony in the east and they dispatch their submarine fleet to reign the Canadians in. title: Pinto e Shamy- Tears of star
des: This story is set inside an enormous galaxy, without name and without stars... untill now. The astronomical bodies are the characters: they have feelings, emotions, fears and dreams. In this short, animated video you can see a sort of trailer of the book and of the movie that I want to realize.I live in Italy and I'm searching for a producer who loves the story and wants to believe in it.I want to preserve the natural beauty of the cosmos and I don't want to transform into a cartoon for children:the story can be appreciate from kids and children, but it is not only for them. I think that motion capture could be a good way to ricreate emotions in the astronomical bodies,designed with a good and smart use of the computer.The book and the movie should link common people to the wonder of the universe and let the public consider scientific phenomenas from a new view,giving a sensitive answer for eclipses,explosions or the light. It's the first part of a saga and the plot explores what happens after the happy ending: the main focus is on the realization of the dreams of the characters and how life changes when the love, happiness and pleasure guide it.
